From Beyond The Grave 1974.
The multipart From Beyond the Grave features Peter Cushing as the owner of a 
sinister antique shop. Utilizing the various artifacts in his establishment, 
Cushing metes out retribution to customers who try to bamboozle him. The 
quartet of horror playlets included herein are "The Gate Crasher," "An Act 
of Kindness," "The Elemental," and "The Door"; all originally appeared in 
short-story form in Ronald Chetwynd-Hayes' The Unbidden. The British cast 
includes David Warner, Donald Pleasence, Ian Bannen, Diana Dors, Nyree Dawn 
Porter, Ian Carmichael, Ian Ogilvy, Lesley-Anne Down, and Margaret Leighton. 
This Amicus production was also released as Creatures and The Creatures 
from Beyond the Grave.
